Questions:
What is the primary objective of the research study involving metformin for adolescents with acute lymphoblastic leukemia?
A) To determine the best dosage of metformin for daily consumption;
B) To assess the impact of metformin on the quality of life in adolescents;
C) To investigate whether metformin can decrease the expression of ABCB1 and AMPK genes in leukemia cells;
D) To compare the effectiveness of metformin against other standard leukemia treatments.

Correct answer: C

If you choose not to participate in the metformin study, what is the standard care option available for adolescents with acute lymphoblastic leukemia at the General Hospital of Mexico "Dr. Eduardo Liceaga"?
A) The patient will not receive any treatment for leukemia;
B) The patient will receive the standard chemotherapy regimen without the addition of metformin;
C) The patient will only receive supportive care without chemotherapy;
D) The patient will be referred to another institution for alternative experimental treatments.

Correct answer: B

How will the confidentiality of the patient's records be handled in this study?
A) Patient records will be made public for educational purposes;
B) Patient records will be shared with all hospital staff regardless of their involvement in the study;
C) Patient records will be kept confidential and only used by the research team for study purposes;
D) Patient records will be disclosed to third-party advertisers for marketing purposes.

Correct answer: C) Patient records will be kept confidential and only used by the research team for study purposes.

If a participant or their guardian has questions about the patient's rights in the research project, whom should they contact?

A) The hospital's general information desk;
B) Dr. Antonia Cervantes Barrios, President of the Research Ethics Committee;
C) The participant's primary care physician;
D) The local health department.

Correct answer: B) Dr. Antonia Cervantes Barrios, President of the Research Ethics Committee.
